author: The Bulletin
title: Local roundup: Overtime goal lifts ECSU soccer to win
text: • H.S. girls roundup: Fitch volleyball edges East Lyme to stay undefeated... MANSFIELD — Jamie Belden scored following a corner kick at the 105:45 mark of double overtime to give Eastern Connecticut State a 2-1 win over Trinity on Wednesday night for its fifth win in six games. Maggie Bodington scored the first goal for the Warriors (9-3-1). East Lyme graduate Rachel Skelton made seven saves to earn her ninth victory of the season. Woodstock Academy alum Emily Becher had two shots on goal. WOMEN’S VOLLEYBALL UConn 3 Temple 2 STORRS — Rebecca River dished out 29 assists to go along with 13 digs and the Huskies won a back-and-forth contest against the Owls, 23-25, 25-18, 24-26, 25-15, 17-15, to snap a three-match losing streak at the start of a four-match homestand. Emma Turner added 23 assists, Kenya Cason had 16 kills and Jade Strawberry and Danielle Cabel each had 12 kills for UConn (8-10, 2-5 American Athletic Conference). PRO LACROSSE Black Wolves to play exhibition game in Pa. NEW YORK — The National Lacrosse League announced that the New England Black Wolves and Buffalo Bandits will play an exhibition game at the PPL Center in Allentown, Pa. at 7 p.m. on Dec. 19. The Black Wolves open the season in Vancouver at 10 p.m. on Jan. 9. No other preseason games have been announced. By The Bulletin
